â Set a valid failsafe source address (F_Source_Add). â Set the same failsafe source address in the fieldbus master and fieldbus slave
FuncSafetyError-67 Watchdog time for PROFIsafe communication (F_WD_Time, F_WD_Time_2) is 0 ms

â Acknowledge the warning. â Establish safe communication again. â If the warning occurs repeatedly, switch the device off and on again. For further support, contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service

E-0 No fault
E-1 Output stage monitoring
E-1.1 Short circuit in motor output terminals 'Overcurrent in output stage or faulty output stage control detected, and output stage inhibited by hardware'
Possible causes for overcurrent are short circuit at the output, excessive motor current, or a defective power output stage

E-1.2 Overcurrent in output stage 'Motor current too high, Current supply, Current transformer, Ramp limit deactivated and set ramp time too short, Phase module defective, DC 24 V supply voltage instable, Interruption or short circuit on signal lines of phase modules'
Connect a smaller motor, Check the current supply, Check the current transformer, Increase the ramp time, Check the phase module, Check the DC 24 V supply voltage, Check the signal lines
E-3 Ground fault
E-3.1 Ground fault 'Ground fault in the motor lead, Ground fault in the inverter, Ground fault in the motor, Ground fault in line components'
Eliminate ground fault in motor lead, Eliminate ground fault in inverter, Eliminate ground fault in motor, Eliminate ground fault in line components
E-4 Brake chopper
E-4.1 Brake chopper overcurrent 'Excessive regenerative power, Short circuit detected in braking resistor circuit, Braking resistor impedance too low'
Extend the deceleration ramps, Check supply cable to braking resistor, Check the technical data of the braking resistor
E-4.2 Brake chopper defective 'Output stage of brake chopper defective'
Replace the defective brake chopper
E-6 Line fault
E-6.1 Line phase failure 'Missing line phase detected, DC link voltage periodically too low, Inadequate line voltage quality'
Check the power supply cable, Check the configuration of the supply system, Check supply (fuses, contactor)
E-7 DC link
E-7.2 DC link discharge failed 'DC link voltage level not dropped below discharge threshold within discharge time'
Contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service
E-7.1 DC link overvoltage 'Maximum permitted DC link voltage limit exceeded and output stage inhibited by hardware'
â Extend the deceleration ramps. â Check the supply cable to the braking resistor. â Check the technical data of the braking resistor
E-8 Speed monitoring

E-8.1 Speed monitoring â motor mode 'Speed controller operates at setting limit (mechanical overload or phase failure in supply system or motor), Encoder not connected correctly, Encoder has incorrect direction of rotation'

Increase the delay time set for speed monitoring, or reduce the load, Check encoder connection and direction of rotation. If necessary, increase current limiting or reduce acceleration values, â Check encoder connection and direction of rotation. If necessary, increase current limiting or reduce acceleration values. â Check motor lead and motor, check line phases

E-8.2 Speed monitoring â generator mode 'Speed controller operates at setting limit (mechanical overload or phase failure in supply system or motor), Encoder not connected correctly, Encoder has incorrect direction of rotation'

Increase the delay time set for speed monitoring, or reduce the regenerative load, Check encoder connection and direction of rotation. If necessary, increase current limiting or reduce deceleration values, â Check encoder connection and direction of rotation. If necessary, increase current limiting or reduce deceleration values. â Check motor lead and motor, check line phases
E-8.3 Maximum speed at motor shaft 'Actual speed exceeded 'Maximum speed at motor shaft' limit (index 8360.9/8361.9). This limit value is set at startup matching motor and gear unit'
Reduce the maximum rotational speed
E-9 Control mode
E-9.11 Standstill current function 'With the ELSM method, the standstill current function is only possible in combination with rotor position measurement'
â Activate rotor position measuring. â Check the motor data
E-9.10 Rotor stall monitoring 'Current control cannot hold load torque. Deviation between stationary setpoint voltage and actual voltage too large'
Reduce the load torque (hoist) in the controlled system

E-9.2 Requested operating mode not possible with active control mode 'Current FCB activated an operating mode. The active control mode does not support this operating mode, for example 'position control' or 'torque control' with V/f control mode'
â Use a control mode that allows the required operating mode. You might have to connect an encoder. â Choose an operating mode that is supported by the current control mode

E-9.9 Parameter measurement not possible with active motor type 'Parameter measurement is only possible for asynchronous and synchronous motor types. Parameter measurement is not possible for reluctance motors and LSPM motors'
Select the correct motor type
E-9.5 Maximum output frequency exceeded 'Maximum output frequency exceeded'
Reduce the maximum rotational speed
E-9.6 Maximum model speed exceeded 'Speed of drive calculated in ELSMÂ® control mode too high for motor control'
If possible minimize the 'Speed/position controller sampling cycle', or reduce the speed
E-9.1 Magnetization of motor not possible 'User-defined current limit or output stage monitoring reduced possible maximum current to such a degree that required magnetizing current cannot be set'
â Reduce output stage utilization e.g. by reducing the PWM frequency or reducing the load. â Increase user-defined current limit
E-9.8 Motor protection function â demagnetization 'Rotor flux calculated by motor model not plausible, or calculated internal voltage too small'

â Check the configuration data. â Check the motor data. â Check the machine: standstill or speed too low. â Check the connection cable between inverter and motor. â Contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service
E-9.4 Correct current supply of motor not possible 'Failed to set required current during premagnetization'
â Check the cabling. â Disable the 'Current monitoring during premagnetization' function. â Disable the 'Current monitoring during initial position determination' function
E-9.3 Absolute rotor position not available 'Active control mode requires absolute rotor position. Encoder selected under 'Actual rotational speed source' does not provide absolute rotor position'
Use an absolute encoder, or identify the rotor position using FCB 18
E-10 Data Flexibility
E-10.99 Unknown error 'Unknown Data Flexibility error'
Contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service
E-10.4 Stack 'Overflow of Data Flexibility stack detected'
Check the program
E-10.10 Setpoint cycle time not supported 'Non-supported setpoint cycle time parameterized'
Set the setpoint cycle time to the default value 1 ms
E-10.12 Runtime warning 'The program requires more runtime than has been configured'
Check the program
E-10.6 Runtime 'Runtime error/watchdog, PDI or PDO tasks'
Check the program. The program execution time exceeds the permitted time, Check the program. The execution time of the PDI or PDO task exceeds the permitted time
E-10.11 No application program loaded 'No Data Flexibility application program loaded'
Load the program or disable Data Flexibility

E-10.7 Calculation result of multiplication/division command too large 'Calculation result of multiplication/division command exceeds 32 bits, Failed to write calculation result of multiplication/division command into result variable'
Check the program
E-10.3 Memory access 'Memory area violated while accessing array'
An array access, for example, results in writing beyond the permitted memory range. Check the program
E-10.1 Initialization 'Init task error'
Init task provided return code != 0. Check the program

E-10.2 Illegal operation code 'Unknown program command (illegal opcode) detected in Data Flexibility program, The version of the MOVIKITÂ® software module in use does not run with the current firmware version of the device'

Contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service, â Use the latest firmware version of the device. â Adjust the firmware version of the device according to the version overview in the installation instructions. â Adjust the version of the MOVIKITÂ® software module according to the version overview in the installation instructions. â In the context menu of the device, select the menu item 'Adjust version and device'
E-10.8 Illegal connection 'Index used in connect not allowed'
Check the program. The index used either does not exist or is not permitted for access via process data, see parameter list
E-10.5 Division by 0 'Division by 0'
Check the program
E-10.9 CRC code 'Wrong CRC checksum of code'
Load the program again. The program memory is corrupt. Invalid write access to the program memory
E-11 Temperature monitoring
E-11.10 Wire break at temperature sensor of signal electronics 'Wire break at temperature sensor of signal electronics'
Contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service
E-11.11 Short circuit at temperature sensor of signal electronics 'Short circuit at temperature sensor of signal electronics'
Contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service
E-11.9 Signal electronics overtemperature 'Maximum permitted signal electronics temperature exceeded'
â Reduce the load. â Reduce the ambient temperature
E-11.2 Heat sink utilization â prewarning 'High thermal load on heat sink of device, and prewarning threshold reached'
â Reduce the load. â Reduce the rms value of the current. â Reduce the PWM frequency. â Ensure sufficient cooling. â Reduce the ambient temperature
E-11.7 Wire break at temperature sensor of heat sink 'Wire break at temperature sensor of heat sink'
Contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service
E-11.8 Short circuit at temperature sensor of heat sink 'Short circuit at temperature sensor of heat sink'
Contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service
E-11.1 Heat sink overtemperature 'Maximum permitted heat sink temperature exceeded. Capacity utilization possibly too high'
â Reduce the load. â Reduce the rms value of the current. â Reduce the PWM frequency. â Ensure sufficient cooling. â Reduce the ambient temperature
E-11.6 Electromechanical utilization â prewarning 'High load on electromechanical components of device due to high continuous current. Prewarning threshold reached'
â Reduce the load. â Reduce the PWM frequency. â Reduce the rms value of the current. â Reduce the ambient temperature
E-11.5 Electromechanical utilization 'Electromechanical components of device overloaded by excessive continuous current'
Reduce the load. If necessary, reduce the rms value of the current

E-11.3 Device utilization 'Temperature reached or exceeded switch-off threshold. Mean output current too high, PWM frequency too high, Ambient temperature too high, Unfavorable air convection, Fan defective'
â Reduce the load. â Check the combination of motor and inverter, Reduce the PWM frequency, Ensure sufficient cooling, Check air convection, Check the fan and replace if necessary
E-12 Brake
E-12.5 Short circuit 'Short circuit detected on the brake'
Check the brake connection
E-12.7 Overcurrent 'Brake coil defective, The brake requires more current than the electronics (inverter or BGI) can supply'
Replace the brake, â Check the parameter setting of the brake. â Use electronics of a larger size. â Use a brake with a larger coil resistance
E-12.4 Brake control module missing 'Brake control has been activated although the hardware is not equipped with the matching module'
Select another brake type or brake connection
E-12.22 Digital motor integration warning 'The intelligent brake rectifier of digital motor integration signaled a warning'
For the exact cause of the fault and for information on how to correct the problem, refer to the fault detected by the subcomponent
E-12.23 Digital motor integration timeout 'Communication with intelligent brake rectifier disrupted'
Check the connection
E-12.24 Digitale Motorintegration Initialisierung 'Die Initialisierung des intelligenten Bremsgleichrichters ist fehlgeschlagen'
â Fehler quittieren. â Bei wiederholtem Auftreten des Fehlers wenden Sie sich an den Service von SEW-EURODRIVE
E-12.21 Digital motor integration fault 'The intelligent brake rectifier of digital motor integration has detected a component fault'
For the exact cause of the fault and for information on how to correct the problem, refer to the fault detected by the subcomponent
E-12.20 Digital motor integration fault â critical 'The intelligent brake rectifier of digital motor integration has detected a critical component fault'
For the exact cause of the fault and for information on how to correct the problem, refer to the fault detected by the subcomponent
E-12.2 DC 24 V brake voltage 'DC 24 V supply voltage not within permitted tolerance of Â± 10%, Monitoring is only active with parameter settings âBrake installedâ and âBrake appliedâ'
Check the DC 24 V supply voltage, Check parameter setting

E-12.3 Temperature 'Brake temperature outside permitted range (too high or too low), In decentralized devices, the overvoltage of the DC link is reduced via the brake. The temperature of the brake is therefore too high'
Check the ambient conditions and the application, Check the application for how often generator mode occurs
E-12.9 Plausibility error 'No brake connected, Brake connected incorrectly, Wrong brake taken into operation'
Connect a brake, Check and correct the brake connection, Check startup

E-12.1 Brake output fault 'No brake connected, Brake cable disconnected in switched-on state, The brake was overloaded by an overcurrent > 2 A, The brake was overloaded by frequent connection (> 0.5 Hz), Monitoring works only with parameter setting 'Brake installed' and 'Brake applied''
Check the connection of the brake, Check the sequential profile of brake control, Make sure that the connected brake is permitted
E-13 Encoder 1
E-13.2 Unknown encoder type 'Encoder type not known and not supported by inverter'

â Check the encoder type. â Contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.4 Track measurement error 'Error during track measurement'

â Switch the device off and on again. â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources (e.g. from EMC). â Check the encoder. Replace if necessary.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.15 System error 'System error while evaluating encoder'

â Make sure that multi-turn encoder is within the configured track area. â Check the limits. â Check for correct setting of encoder numerator/denominator factors. â Check interference sources (e.g. from EMC). â Check the startup parameters. â Switch the device off and on again. â If the fault occurs repeatedly, contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.67 SSI encoder â warning 'The SSI encoder signaled a warning'

â Check the startup parameters. â Check the settings of the SSI encoder. â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources (light beam interrupted, reflector, data cables, etc.). â Replace the encoder.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.21 SSI encoder â fault 'SSI encoder signaled a fault'

â Check the startup parameters. â Check the settings of the SSI encoder. â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources (light beam interrupted, reflector, data cables, etc.). â Replace the encoder.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.20 SSI encoder â critical fault 'SSI encoder signaled a critical fault'

â Check the startup parameters. â Check the settings of the SSI encoder. â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources (light beam interrupted, reflector, data cables, etc.). â Replace the encoder.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.6 Signal level too low 'The amount resulting from the level of the two track signals A and B is lower than the permissible limit'

â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources (e.g. from EMC). â Check the encoder.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.7 Signal level too high 'The amount resulting from the level of the two track signals A and B exceeds the permissible limit'

Check the gear ratio of the resolver in use.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.8 Signal level monitoring 'The amount resulting from the level of the two track signals A and B exceeds the permissible limit'

Check the mounting position of the resolver.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.9 Quadrant check 'Error checking quadrants (sine encoder)'

â Switch the device off and on again. â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources (e.g. from EMC). â Check the encoder. Replace if necessary.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.24 Travel range exceeded 'Current position mode does not allow for larger travel range'

Check the travel range.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.29 Absolute position invalid 'Diagnostics error detected while evaluating absolute encoder position. Referencing is canceled'

â Reference the drive again. â If the error occurs repeatedly, contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.1 Position comparison check 'Fault detected when comparing raw position and track counter of absolute encoder'

â Check the wiring of track signals. â Check interference sources (e.g. from EMC). â Replace the encoder. â Replace the encoder card.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.10 Position tolerance range exceeded 'Position outside tolerance range'

â Check the startup parameters. â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources (light beam interrupted, reflector, data cables, etc.). â Replace the encoder.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.3 Invalid data 'Invalid encoder nameplate data (measuring steps/pulses per revolution/multi-turn)'

â Check the startup parameters. â Replace the encoder.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.5 Internal warning 'Encoder signaled warning'
â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources (light beam interrupted, reflector, data cables, etc.). â Clean the sensor
E-13.23 Internal fault 'Encoder deteced internal fault'

â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources (light beam interrupted, reflector, data cables, etc.). â Replace the encoder.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.22 Internal fault â critical 'Encoder deteced internal fault'

â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources (light beam interrupted, reflector, data cables, etc.). â Replace the encoder.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.13 Initialization error 'Communication error during initialization'

When using encoders of SEW-EURODRIVE: â Check the wiring.
When using encoders of other manufacturers: â Check the wiring. â Check the parameter setting in MOVISUITEÂ®. â Check whether the settings via DIP switches, display, USB interface, etc. on the encoder match the information in the operating instructions for the inverter or the option (e.g. baud rate, node ID).
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.51 Safety card encoder warning 'Encoder fault detected while drive safety function is inactive'
â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources. â Apply the shield of the encoder cable over a large area. â Check the encoder
E-13.55 Level monitoring 'Track signal level not within tolerance band'
â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources. â Apply the shield of the encoder cable over a large area. â Check the encoder

E-13.73 Encoder range overflow pending 'The encoder is just before overflow. The system is too fast. The position difference is above the 1/4 encoder range. With 1/2 encoder range, an undetected reversal of the direction of rotation occurs and consequently a permanent error in position'
â Reduce the system speed. â Use an encoder with a larger encoder measuring range (resolution/multi-turn range)
E-13.52 Encoder signal fault 'Unexpected encoder signals'
â Check the wiring. â Check interference sources. â Apply the shield of the encoder cable over a large area. â Check the encoder

E-13.71 Response time of safety card exceeded 'The response time for calculating the speed or acceleration cannot be adhered to. This can have the following reasons: â The safety card has received more corrupt telegrams from the encoder than the error tolerance allows. â The actual refresh time of the encoder is greater than parameterized'

â Check the wiring. â Check the encoder. â Adjust the refresh time to the values in the encoder documentation. â If the fault occurs repeatedly, replace the safety card and send it together with the fault number to SEW-EURODRIVE. For further support, contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service.
NOTE In 'emergency mode' manual mode, you can move the drive using the motor encoder if the external position encoder is faulty
E-13.72 Internal fault â overflow during position detection 'Overflow detected during internal calculation of the position'
Adjust the startup parameters, for example: â Numerator scaling/denominator scaling of the encoder. â User units of the position
E-13.68 Internal fault â overflow 'Overflow detected during internal calculation'
Adjust the startup parameters, such as numerator scaling/denominator scaling
E-13.66 No position code visible 'Optical encoder cannot decode valid barcode/matrix code in field of view'

â Check the code tape for damage (e.g. gaps, covering, soiling, reflecting materials, or ambient light sources). â Check the optical system of the encoder for damage or dirt. â Check diagnostic data indicating faulty assembly. â Check the encoder for proper mounting, such as distance to the code tape, lateral offset or twisting. â To make the system more robust, increase the value of the 'Threshold for tolerated faults â PXV encoder'. â If the fault occurs repeatedly, replace the encoder and send it together with the fault number to SEW-EURODRIVE. For further support, contact SEW-EURODRIVE Service
E-13.56 Maximum speed exceeded while encoder fault muting is active 'Maximum permitted speed exceeded and encoder fault muting active'
â Check the maximum speed of the application while encoder fault muting is active and adjust, if necessary. â Check the parameter setting of the safety card and adjust it, if necessary
E-13.57 Maximum speed exceeded 'Maximum permitted speed exceeded'
â Check the maximum speed of the application and adjust it, if necessary. â Check the parameter setting of the safety card and adjust it, if necessary
E-13.53 Maximum frequency exceeded 'Maximum permitted signal frequency exceeded'
